@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home";
}

<div class="container mt-4">
    <h1 class="mb-3">MVC Product Catalog Demo</h1>

    <p class="lead">
        This application demonstrates a classic ASP.NET Core MVC CRUD workflow
        with validation, error handling, and clean navigation.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h4>A. Check main functionality (CRUD)</h4>
    <p>
        Open the Products section to view, create, edit, and delete products.
    </p>
    <a asp-controller="Product" asp-action="Index">
        Go to Products
    </a>

    <hr />

    <h4>B. Check validation</h4>
    <p>
        Validation is implemented using model attributes and server-side checks.
        Try creating or editing a product with invalid data:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Leave <strong>Name</strong> empty</li>
        <li>Enter a negative or zero <strong>Price</strong></li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        Validation errors will be displayed directly in the form.
    </p>
    <a asp-controller="Product" asp-action="Create">
        Try Create with invalid data
    </a>

    <hr />

    <h4>C. Check error handling</h4>
    <p>
        The application uses centralized error handling with custom error pages.
        You can test it using the following links:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <a asp-controller="Product" asp-action="Details" asp-route-id="9999">
                Product not found (404)
            </a>
        </li>
        <li>
            <a asp-controller="Product" asp-action="Edit" asp-route-id="0">
                Invalid request (400)
            </a>
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="/some-random-page">
                Unknown page (404)
            </a>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        All errors are handled via <code>/Error/{code}</code> with dedicated views.
    </p>
</div>

